ronmental health research should be protected from capture by any single interest group.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChemicalsxLaw and legislation. 0aChemicalsxSafety measures. 0aEconomics. 0aEnvironmental health. 0aHealth risk assessment. 0aPhenolsxToxicology. 0aPhenols. 0aPolitics, Practical. 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / Health Care Issues.2bisacsh  aamerican culture.  aamerican society.  abpa plastic.  acoffee table books.  adangers of plastic.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  aeconomics and science.  aeducational books.  aengaging.  agoing green.  ahealth care issues.  ahealth fitness.  ahealth policy.  ahome school science books.  ainformative reading.  ais plastic safe.  alearning from experts.  anonfiction reading.  apage turner.  aplastic in environment.  apolitics and science.  apublic health books.  aquarantine books.  asafety guide.  asaving the planet.  ascience and math.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095420540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520954205423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520954205/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles